{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01MPK1WYh88PDNdj4nmdhiP5","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect! Here's the complete exploration of the shared crate:\n\n## Shared Crate Structure\n\nAll files located at `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/solana/shared/src/`:\n\n1. **commit_reveal.rs**\n2. **constants.rs**\n3. **cpi.rs**\n4. **escrow.rs**\n5. **fees.rs**\n6. **lib.rs**\n7. **lifecycle.rs**\n8. **pause.rs**\n9. **tiers.rs**\n10. **timeout.rs**\n11. **vrf_orao.rs**\n\n---\n\n## File Contents\n\n### 1. lib.rs\n```rust\npub mod commit_reveal;\npub mod constants;\npub mod cpi;\npub mod escrow;\npub mod fees;\npub mod lifecycle;\npub mod pause;\npub mod tiers;\npub mod timeout;\npub mod vrf_orao;\n```\n\n**Purpose**: Module exports for all shared utilities.\n\n---\n\n### 2. tiers.rs\n```rust\nuse anchor_lang::prelude::*;\n\n/// Fixed tier entry amounts in lamports.\n/// Index 0 = Iron, 1 = Bronze, 2 = Silver, 3 = Gold, 4 = Platinum, 5 = Diamond\npub const TIER_AMOUNTS: [u64; 6] = [\n    5_000_000,       // 0.005 SOL — Iron\n    10_000_000,      // 0.01  SOL — Bronze\n    100_000_000,     // 0.1   SOL — Silver\n    250_000_000,     // 0.25  SOL — Gold\n    500_000_000,     // 0.5   SOL — Platinum\n    1_000_000_000,   // 1.0   SOL — Diamond\n];\n\npub const TIER_COUNT: usize = TIER_AMOUNTS.len();\n\n/// Returns the entry amount for the given tier index, or an error if out of range.\npub fn get_tier_amount(tier: u8) -> Result<u64> {\n    TIER_AMOUNTS\n        .get(tier as usize)\n        .copied()\n        .ok_or_else(|| error!(TierError::InvalidTier))\n}\n\n#[error_code]\npub enum TierError {\n    #[msg(\"Invalid tier index\")]\n    InvalidTier,\n}\n```\n\n**Purpose**: Defines tier entry amounts in lamports (0.005 to 1.0 SOL) and provides utility to get tier amount with validation.\n\n---\n\n### 3. lifecycle.rs\n```rust\nuse anchor_lang::prelude::*;\n\n/// Lifecycle phase for every round/match in any game.\n#[derive(AnchorSerialize, AnchorDeserialize, Clone, Copy, PartialEq, Eq, Debug, InitSpace)]\npub enum RoundPhase {\n    Waiting,\n    Active,\n    Locked,\n    Resolving,\n    Settled,\n    Refunded,\n}\n\n/// Timestamps tracking round progression.\n#[derive(AnchorSerialize, AnchorDeserialize, Clone, Copy, Debug)]\npub struct RoundTimestamps {\n    pub created_at: i64,\n    pub locked_at: Option<i64>,\n    pub resolve_deadline: Option<i64>,\n    pub settled_at: Option<i64>,\n}\n\n#[error_code]\npub enum LifecycleError {\n    #[msg(\"Invalid phase transition\")]\n    InvalidTransition,\n}\n\n/// Validates that the transition from `current` to `target` is allowed.\n///\n/// Allowed transitions:\n/// - Waiting → Active, Locked, Refunded\n/// - Active → Locked, Refunded\n/// - Locked → Resolving, Refunded\n/// - Resolving → Settled, Refunded\n///\n/// LOCKED → SETTLED is explicitly disallowed; VRF games read the result\n/// at claim time and set the phase directly.\npub fn transition(current: RoundPhase, target: RoundPhase) -> Result<()> {\n    let valid = matches!(\n        (current, target),\n        (RoundPhase::Waiting, RoundPhase::Active)\n            | (RoundPhase::Waiting, RoundPhase::Locked)\n            | (RoundPhase::Active, RoundPhase::Locked)\n            | (RoundPhase::Locked, RoundPhase::Resolving)\n            | (RoundPhase::Resolving, RoundPhase::Settled)\n            | (RoundPhase::Resolving, RoundPhase::Refunded)\n            | (RoundPhase::Waiting, RoundPhase::Refunded)\n            | (RoundPhase::Active, RoundPhase::Refunded)\n            | (RoundPhase::Locked, RoundPhase::Refunded)\n    );\n\n    if valid {\n        Ok(())\n    } else {\n        Err(LifecycleError::InvalidTransition.into())\n    }\n}\n\n#[cfg(test)]\nmod tests {\n    use super::*;\n\n    #[test]\n    fn valid_transitions() {\n        assert!(transition(RoundPhase::Waiting, RoundPhase::Active).is_ok());\n        assert!(transition(RoundPhase::Waiting, RoundPhase::Locked).is_ok());\n        assert!(transition(RoundPhase::Active, RoundPhase::Locked).is_ok());\n        assert!(transition(RoundPhase::Locked, RoundPhase::Resolving).is_ok());\n        assert!(transition(RoundPhase::Resolving, RoundPhase::Settled).is_ok());\n        assert!(transition(RoundPhase::Resolving, RoundPhase::Refunded).is_ok());\n        assert!(transition(RoundPhase::Waiting, RoundPhase::Refunded).is_ok());\n        assert!(transition(RoundPhase::Active, RoundPhase::Refunded).is_ok());\n        assert!(transition(RoundPhase::Locked, RoundPhase::Refunded).is_ok());\n    }\n\n    #[test]\n    fn invalid_transitions() {\n        // Self-transitions\n        assert!(transition(RoundPhase::Waiting, RoundPhase::Waiting).is_err());\n        assert!(transition(RoundPhase::Locked, RoundPhase::Locked).is_err());\n\n        // Backward transitions\n        assert!(transition(RoundPhase::Active, RoundPhase::Waiting).is_err());\n        assert!(transition(RoundPhase::Locked, RoundPhase::Waiting).is_err());\n        assert!(transition(RoundPhase::Settled, RoundPhase::Waiting).is_err());\n\n        // LOCKED → SETTLED explicitly invalid (VRF games use claim, not transition)\n        assert!(transition(RoundPhase::Locked, RoundPhase::Settled).is_err());\n\n        // Terminal states cannot transition\n        assert!(transition(RoundPhase::Settled, RoundPhase::Refunded).is_err());\n        assert!(transition(RoundPhase::Refunded, RoundPhase::Settled).is_err());\n\n        // Skip transitions\n        assert!(transition(RoundPhase::Waiting, RoundPhase::Settled).is_err());\n        assert!(transition(RoundPhase::Waiting, RoundPhase::Resolving).is_err());\n    }\n\n    #[test]\n    fn enum_serialization_roundtrip() {\n        let phases = [\n            RoundPhase::Waiting,\n            RoundPhase::Active,\n            RoundPhase::Locked,\n            RoundPhase::Resolving,\n            RoundPhase::Settled,\n            RoundPhase::Refunded,\n        ];\n\n        for phase in phases {\n            let mut buf = Vec::new();\n            AnchorSerialize::serialize(&phase, &mut buf).unwrap();\n            let deserialized = RoundPhase::deserialize(&mut buf.as_slice()).unwrap();\n            assert_eq!(phase, deserialized);\n        }\n    }\n}\n```\n\n**Purpose**: Defines game round lifecycle phases (Waiting → Active → Locked → Resolving → Settled/Refunded) and enforces valid state transitions. Includes timestamp tracking.\n\n---\n\n### 4. fees.rs\n```rust\n/// Compile-time safety cap: no fee can ever exceed 10% (1000 bps).\npub const MAX_FEE_BPS: u16 = 1000;\n\n/// Total platform fee: 3% (300 basis points)\n/// - 200 bps: platform revenue\n/// - 70 bps: rakeback pool (raid boss rewards)\n/// - 30 bps: chest treasury\npub const TOTAL_FEE_BPS: u16 = 300;\npub const REVENUE_BPS: u16 = 200;\npub const RAKEBACK_BPS: u16 = 70;\npub const CHEST_BPS: u16 = 30;\n\n// Compile-time assertion: fee must never exceed safety cap.\nconst _: () = assert!(TOTAL_FEE_BPS <= MAX_FEE_BPS);\n\n/// Calculate the total fee for a given amount.\n/// Returns the fee in lamports.\npub fn calculate_fee(amount: u64) -> u64 {\n    (amount as u128 * TOTAL_FEE_BPS as u128 / 10_000) as u64\n}\n\n/// Calculate fee and net payout for a given pool amount.\n/// Returns `(fee, net_payout)` where `net_payout = pool - fee`.\n/// Fee rounds down (integer division truncates), favoring the player.\npub fn calculate_net_payout(pool: u64) -> (u64, u64) {\n    let fee = calculate_fee(pool);\n    (fee, pool - fee)\n}\n\n/// Split a fee amount into (revenue, rakeback, chest).\npub fn split_fee(fee: u64) -> (u64, u64, u64) {\n    let revenue = (fee as u128 * REVENUE_BPS as u128 / TOTAL_FEE_BPS as u128) as u64;\n    let rakeback = (fee as u128 * RAKEBACK_BPS as u128 / TOTAL_FEE_BPS as u128) as u64;\n    let chest = fee - revenue - rakeback; // remainder avoids rounding loss\n    (revenue, rakeback, chest)\n}\n\n#[cfg(test)]\nmod tests {\n    use super::*;\n\n    #[test]\n    fn test_calculate_fee() {\n        assert_eq!(calculate_fee(10_000), 300);\n        assert_eq!(calculate_fee(1_000_000), 30_000);\n        assert_eq!(calculate_fee(0), 0);\n    }\n\n    #[test]\n    fn test_calculate_net_payout() {\n        let (fee, net) = calculate_net_payout(1_000_000);\n        assert_eq!(fee, 30_000);\n        assert_eq!(net, 970_000);\n        assert_eq!(fee + net, 1_000_000);\n\n        // Zero pool\n        let (fee, net) = calculate_net_payout(0);\n        assert_eq!(fee, 0);\n        assert_eq!(net, 0);\n\n        // Small amount where rounding truncates (favors player)\n        // 100 lamports * 300 / 10000 = 3.0 exactly\n        let (fee, net) = calculate_net_payout(100);\n        assert_eq!(fee, 3);\n        assert_eq!(net, 97);\n\n        // Non-round amount: 1 lamport → fee rounds to 0\n        let (fee, net) = calculate_net_payout(1);\n        assert_eq!(fee, 0);\n        assert_eq!(net, 1);\n    }\n\n    #[test]\n    fn test_max_fee_bps_cap() {\n        assert!(TOTAL_FEE_BPS <= MAX_FEE_BPS);\n    }\n\n    #[test]\n    fn test_split_fee() {\n        let (rev, rake, chest) = split_fee(300);\n        assert_eq!(rev, 200);\n        assert_eq!(rake, 70);\n        assert_eq!(chest, 30);\n        assert_eq!(rev + rake + chest, 300);\n    }\n}\n```\n\n**Purpose**: Hardcoded fee constants (3% total: 200 bps revenue, 70 bps rakeback, 30 bps chest) with utility functions for fee calculation, net payout, and fee splitting.\n\n---\n\n### 5. escrow.rs\n```rust\nuse anchor_lang::prelude::*;\nuse anchor_lang::system_program;\n\n/// Error codes for escrow operations.\n#[error_code]\npub enum EscrowError {\n    /// The escrow PDA does not hold enough lamports for the requested transfer.\n    #[msg(\"Insufficient escrow balance\")]\n    InsufficientEscrowBalance,\n}\n\n/// Transfers lamports from a PDA to a recipient using direct lamport manipulation.\n///\n/// This is the standard pattern for moving funds out of a program-owned PDA\n/// (e.g., paying out a winner, refunding a player, sending fees to treasury).\n///\n/// # Example\n/// ```ignore\n/// transfer_lamports_from_pda(\n///     &ctx.accounts.coinflip_match.to_account_info(),\n///     &ctx.accounts.winner.to_account_info(),\n///     payout_amount,\n/// )?;\n/// ```\npub fn transfer_lamports_from_pda(\n    pda: &AccountInfo,\n    recipient: &AccountInfo,\n    amount: u64,\n) -> Result<()> {\n    let pda_balance = pda.lamports();\n    require!(pda_balance >= amount, EscrowError::InsufficientEscrowBalance);\n\n    **pda.try_borrow_mut_lamports()? -= amount;\n    **recipient.try_borrow_mut_lamports()? += amount;\n\n    Ok(())\n}\n\n/// Transfers lamports from a signer to a PDA using system program CPI.\n///\n/// This is the standard pattern for depositing funds into an escrow PDA\n/// (e.g., a player funding a match entry).\n///\n/// # Example\n/// ```ignore\n/// transfer_lamports_to_pda(\n///     &ctx.accounts.creator.to_account_info(),\n///     &ctx.accounts.coinflip_match.to_account_info(),\n///     entry_amount,\n///     &ctx.accounts.system_program.to_account_info(),\n/// )?;\n/// ```\npub fn transfer_lamports_to_pda<'a>(\n    from: &AccountInfo<'a>,\n    pda: &AccountInfo<'a>,\n    amount: u64,\n    system_program_info: &AccountInfo<'a>,\n) -> Result<()> {\n    system_program::transfer(\n        CpiContext::new(\n            system_program_info.clone(),\n            system_program::Transfer {\n                from: from.clone(),\n                to: pda.clone(),\n            },\n        ),\n        amount,\n    )\n}\n```\n\n**Purpose**: Escrow utilities for bidirectional lamport transfers—depositing from signer to PDA (via CPI) and withdrawing from PDA to recipient (direct lamport manipulation).\n\n---\n\n## Summary Table\n\n| Module | Key Exports | Purpose |\n|--------|------------|---------|\n| **tiers.rs** | `TIER_AMOUNTS[6]`, `get_tier_amount()` | 6 entry tiers: 0.005 to 1.0 SOL |\n| **lifecycle.rs** | `RoundPhase` enum, `transition()` | Game round state machine + validation |\n| **fees.rs** | `TOTAL_FEE_BPS`, `calculate_fee()`, `split_fee()` | 3% fee split (200/70/30 bps) |\n| **escrow.rs** | `transfer_lamports_from_pda()`, `transfer_lamports_to_pda()` | Lamport movement utilities |\n\nAll files include comprehensive unit tests validating calculations, state transitions, and edge cases."},{"type":"text","text":"agentId: a3a7f74 (for resuming to continue this agent's work if needed)\n<usage>total_tokens: 35525\ntool_uses: 6\nduration_ms: 29521</usage>"}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"63a7d9fb-5b39-41e7-af6f-c6c9731af600","uuid":"5100040f-cae8-4a18-9723-29c114607a6b","tool_use_result":{"status":"completed","prompt":"Explore the shared crate at `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/solana/shared/src/`. I need:\n1. List all files in the src/ directory\n2. Read lib.rs to understand what's exported\n3. Read the tiers module (whatever file defines tier amounts) \n4. Read the lifecycle module (whatever file defines game phases/lifecycle)\n5. Read the fees module (whatever file defines fee constants)\n6. Read the escrow module\n\nReport the full contents of each file.","agentId":"a3a7f74","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect! Here's the complete exploration of the shared crate:\n\n## Shared Crate Structure\n\nAll files located at `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/solana/shared/src/`:\n\n1. **commit_reveal.rs**\n2. **constants.rs**\n3. **cpi.rs**\n4. **escrow.rs**\n5. **fees.rs**\n6. **lib.rs**\n7. **lifecycle.rs**\n8. **pause.rs**\n9. **tiers.rs**\n10. **timeout.rs**\n11. **vrf_orao.rs**\n\n---\n\n## File Contents\n\n### 1. lib.rs\n```rust\npub mod commit_reveal;\npub mod constants;\npub mod cpi;\npub mod escrow;\npub mod fees;\npub mod lifecycle;\npub mod pause;\npub mod tiers;\npub mod timeout;\npub mod vrf_orao;\n```\n\n**Purpose**: Module exports for all shared utilities.\n\n---\n\n### 2. tiers.rs\n```rust\nuse anchor_lang::prelude::*;\n\n/// Fixed tier entry amounts in lamports.\n/// Index 0 = Iron, 1 = Bronze, 2 = Silver, 3 = Gold, 4 = Platinum, 5 = Diamond\npub const TIER_AMOUNTS: [u64; 6] = [\n    5_000_000,       // 0.005 SOL — Iron\n    10_000_000,      // 0.01  SOL — Bronze\n    100_000_000,     // 0.1   SOL — Silver\n    250_000_000,     // 0.25  SOL — Gold\n    500_000_000,     // 0.5   SOL — Platinum\n    1_000_000_000,   // 1.0   SOL — Diamond\n];\n\npub const TIER_COUNT: usize = TIER_AMOUNTS.len();\n\n/// Returns the entry amount for the given tier index, or an error if out of range.\npub fn get_tier_amount(tier: u8) -> Result<u64> {\n    TIER_AMOUNTS\n        .get(tier as usize)\n        .copied()\n        .ok_or_else(|| error!(TierError::InvalidTier))\n}\n\n#[error_code]\npub enum TierError {\n    #[msg(\"Invalid tier index\")]\n    InvalidTier,\n}\n```\n\n**Purpose**: Defines tier entry amounts in lamports (0.005 to 1.0 SOL) and provides utility to get tier amount with validation.\n\n---\n\n### 3. lifecycle.rs\n```rust\nuse anchor_lang::prelude::*;\n\n/// Lifecycle phase for every round/match in any game.\n#[derive(AnchorSerialize, AnchorDeserialize, Clone, Copy, PartialEq, Eq, Debug, InitSpace)]\npub enum RoundPhase {\n    Waiting,\n    Active,\n    Locked,\n    Resolving,\n    Settled,\n    Refunded,\n}\n\n/// Timestamps tracking round progression.\n#[derive(AnchorSerialize, AnchorDeserialize, Clone, Copy, Debug)]\npub struct RoundTimestamps {\n    pub created_at: i64,\n    pub locked_at: Option<i64>,\n    pub resolve_deadline: Option<i64>,\n    pub settled_at: Option<i64>,\n}\n\n#[error_code]\npub enum LifecycleError {\n    #[msg(\"Invalid phase transition\")]\n    InvalidTransition,\n}\n\n/// Validates that the transition from `current` to `target` is allowed.\n///\n/// Allowed transitions:\n/// - Waiting → Active, Locked, Refunded\n/// - Active → Locked, Refunded\n/// - Locked → Resolving, Refunded\n/// - Resolving → Settled, Refunded\n///\n/// LOCKED → SETTLED is explicitly disallowed; VRF games read the result\n/// at claim time and set the phase directly.\npub fn transition(current: RoundPhase, target: RoundPhase) -> Result<()> {\n    let valid = matches!(\n        (current, target),\n        (RoundPhase::Waiting, RoundPhase::Active)\n            | (RoundPhase::Waiting, RoundPhase::Locked)\n            | (RoundPhase::Active, RoundPhase::Locked)\n            | (RoundPhase::Locked, RoundPhase::Resolving)\n            | (RoundPhase::Resolving, RoundPhase::Settled)\n            | (RoundPhase::Resolving, RoundPhase::Refunded)\n            | (RoundPhase::Waiting, RoundPhase::Refunded)\n            | (RoundPhase::Active, RoundPhase::Refunded)\n            | (RoundPhase::Locked, RoundPhase::Refunded)\n    );\n\n    if valid {\n        Ok(())\n    } else {\n        Err(LifecycleError::InvalidTransition.into())\n    }\n}\n\n#[cfg(test)]\nmod tests {\n    use super::*;\n\n    #[test]\n    fn valid_transitions() {\n        assert!(transition(RoundPhase::Waiting, RoundPhase::Active).is_ok());\n        assert!(transition(RoundPhase::Waiting, RoundPhase::Locked).is_ok());\n        assert!(transition(RoundPhase::Active, RoundPhase::Locked).is_ok());\n        assert!(transition(RoundPhase::Locked, RoundPhase::Resolving).is_ok());\n        assert!(transition(RoundPhase::Resolving, RoundPhase::Settled).is_ok());\n        assert!(transition(RoundPhase::Resolving, RoundPhase::Refunded).is_ok());\n        assert!(transition(RoundPhase::Waiting, RoundPhase::Refunded).is_ok());\n        assert!(transition(RoundPhase::Active, RoundPhase::Refunded).is_ok());\n        assert!(transition(RoundPhase::Locked, RoundPhase::Refunded).is_ok());\n    }\n\n    #[test]\n    fn invalid_transitions() {\n        // Self-transitions\n        assert!(transition(RoundPhase::Waiting, RoundPhase::Waiting).is_err());\n        assert!(transition(RoundPhase::Locked, RoundPhase::Locked).is_err());\n\n        // Backward transitions\n        assert!(transition(RoundPhase::Active, RoundPhase::Waiting).is_err());\n        assert!(transition(RoundPhase::Locked, RoundPhase::Waiting).is_err());\n        assert!(transition(RoundPhase::Settled, RoundPhase::Waiting).is_err());\n\n        // LOCKED → SETTLED explicitly invalid (VRF games use claim, not transition)\n        assert!(transition(RoundPhase::Locked, RoundPhase::Settled).is_err());\n\n        // Terminal states cannot transition\n        assert!(transition(RoundPhase::Settled, RoundPhase::Refunded).is_err());\n        assert!(transition(RoundPhase::Refunded, RoundPhase::Settled).is_err());\n\n        // Skip transitions\n        assert!(transition(RoundPhase::Waiting, RoundPhase::Settled).is_err());\n        assert!(transition(RoundPhase::Waiting, RoundPhase::Resolving).is_err());\n    }\n\n    #[test]\n    fn enum_serialization_roundtrip() {\n        let phases = [\n            RoundPhase::Waiting,\n            RoundPhase::Active,\n            RoundPhase::Locked,\n            RoundPhase::Resolving,\n            RoundPhase::Settled,\n            RoundPhase::Refunded,\n        ];\n\n        for phase in phases {\n            let mut buf = Vec::new();\n            AnchorSerialize::serialize(&phase, &mut buf).unwrap();\n            let deserialized = RoundPhase::deserialize(&mut buf.as_slice()).unwrap();\n            assert_eq!(phase, deserialized);\n        }\n    }\n}\n```\n\n**Purpose**: Defines game round lifecycle phases (Waiting → Active → Locked → Resolving → Settled/Refunded) and enforces valid state transitions. Includes timestamp tracking.\n\n---\n\n### 4. fees.rs\n```rust\n/// Compile-time safety cap: no fee can ever exceed 10% (1000 bps).\npub const MAX_FEE_BPS: u16 = 1000;\n\n/// Total platform fee: 3% (300 basis points)\n/// - 200 bps: platform revenue\n/// - 70 bps: rakeback pool (raid boss rewards)\n/// - 30 bps: chest treasury\npub const TOTAL_FEE_BPS: u16 = 300;\npub const REVENUE_BPS: u16 = 200;\npub const RAKEBACK_BPS: u16 = 70;\npub const CHEST_BPS: u16 = 30;\n\n// Compile-time assertion: fee must never exceed safety cap.\nconst _: () = assert